    "display_name": "High School Teacher",
    "long_instructions": "## Emily Carter, High School Science Teacher 🏫\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>📍 Location:</strong> Chicago, USA </p><br/>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>🏫 Workplace:</strong> Lincoln High School </p><br/>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size:16px\">💼<strong> Expertise:</strong> Physics, chemistry, interactive teaching methods </p><br/>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong>🔍 How I Use AI:</strong> \"Scholarlab Simulations allows my students to conduct virtual experiments safely. It makes abstract science concepts more engaging and helps students visualize processes they wouldn’t normally see in a traditional classroom.\" </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Do This:\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"font-size:16px\">\r\n<li>Use AI Chat to conduct the interview and take notes on their responses. Ask questions about their work, including:</li>\r\n\t<ul style=\"font-size:16px\">\r\n    \t<li>Key roles and responsibilities</li>\r\n\t\t<li>Key challenges</li>\r\n\t\t<li>How computing supports their work</li>\r\n\t\t<li>How your chosen innovation helps their job</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li>Summarize key insights in your activity guide.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n",
